{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic| name=Levicorpus| type=[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Magic#Spells|Spell]]| features=Levitates a person| appearance=[[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Books/Half-Blood Prince|Harry Potter and the Half-Blood Prince]]}}
== Overview ==
{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Beginner Spoiler}}
'''''Levicorpus''''' levitates a victim in the air by their feet.
== Extended Description ==
{{Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Beginner Spoiler}}
This spell is one of the spells that Harry Potter learned from the Half-Blood Prince's ''Advanced Potion-Making'' textbook.
Harry first sees his father, [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/James Potter|James Potter]], use this spell on [[Muggles' Guide to Harry Potter/Characters/Severus Snape|Severus Snape]] in one of Snape's memories. Harry later attempts this spell on Ron not knowing what it would do.
